^2$ $<$ 2.5\nTeV$^{-2}$, $-$8.8 $<$ $c_{\\mathrm{W}}/\\Lambda^2$ $<$ 16 TeV$^{-2}$, and $-$45\n$<$ $c_{\\mathrm{B}}/\\Lambda^2$ $<$ 46 TeV$^{-2}$. These results are combined\nwith the CMS EW Zjj analysis, yielding the constraint on the $c_{\\mathrm{WWW}}$\ncoupling: $-$1.8 $<$ $c_{\\mathrm{WWW}}/\\Lambda^2$ $<$ 2.0 TeV$^{-2}$.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Sun, 10 Mar 2019 18:35:25 GMT"},{"version":"v2","created":"Thu, 23 Jan 2020 14:53:47 GMT"}],"update_date":"2020-01-24"}
