ondensation in the zero-temperature dilute nuclear matter,\nmaking the conventional definition of the symmetry energy meaningless. We\ninvestigate the symmetry energy defined under parabolic approximation for the\nzero-temperature dilute nuclear matter with $\\alpha$-particle condensation, and\nfind it is significantly enhanced compared to the case without clusters and\nbecomes saturated at about $7$ MeV at very low densities ($\\lesssim 10^{-3}$\nfm$^{-3}$). The critical temperature for $\\alpha$-condensation in homogeneous\ndilute nuclear matter is also discussed.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Mon, 11 Mar 2019 03:05:17 GMT"},{"version":"v2","created":"Thu, 24 Oct 2019 00:47:13 GMT"}],"update_date":"2019-11-13"}
